I ordered from Heights Pizza the first time today.  I ordered a cheese pizza with basil and 6 garlic parmesan chicken wings.  I'm not sure why, but I have been craving pizza for two weeks.  I had even participated in Tampa Bay Pizza Week that was held in late March--in search for the best pizza in this area.  The pizza was okay.  I love fresh basil on my pizza because it adds so much flavor.  I hoped the chef here would have put the basil in between the sauce and cheese, but he didn't.  The pizza was good, but it would have tasted better if the basil was underneath the cheese.  I prefer how Cappy's in Seminole Heights makes this pizza.  They know where to place the basil.  I was extremely disappointed with the wings.  I originally wanted lemon pepper wings, but they did not have this option.  So I ordered garlic parmesan.  I hoped the garlic parmesan would have been a dry seasoning rather than wet.  When the woman said it was wet, I said okay---and once I tasted them I was disappointed.  The chef used too much butter and not enough seasoning.  These wings were flavorless.  I could 't even finish it--and I love chicken wings.  Garlic Parmesan should be a dry rub rather than a wet rub.  Customer service was excellent and the prices are reasonable.  I just hope that the chefs read this and modify their recipes.

The only positive thing I could say is that my food was hot when I got it, but I would give my driver more credit for that than anyone else.

BLOODY. RAW. CHICKEN. (not the first person to leave an undercooked chicken review) First let me state that this is already the single-most inconsistent restaurant in Tampa, with a terrible reputation with many people in Seminole Heights who try to frequent it. I am one. I have continued to give the benefit of the doubt for several years as I've watched them slide downhill with everything from sopping-in-grease empanadas, to undercooked pizza, overcooked pizza, wrong toppings, wrong sizes, NO sauce on wings (several times), gross salads, etc. I finally gave up and just ordered one-topping pizzas from here because "how bad could you screw up a pizza?".... until tonight.  I ordered a "free" meal (pizza) (with wings that I paid for) to make up for another order that they butchered, just waited an hour for wings (orders normally only take 30 mins tops to get here), and the bones are absolutely bloody. The chicken is not cooked at all. The response when I called, after my father ate one trusting that it was cooked (because what other job does a restaurant have than to cook food), was "oh I know what happened- the new girl probably mixed up which ones were cooked and which were raw".  ARE YOU KIDDING ME? What kind of sick joke? Would more attention have been paid if the pizza wasn't free? This is no small whoops, but I guarantee everyone will remain working there, though there are a whole laundry list of issues.  POTENTIAL CUSTOMERS-- If you're looking for pizza that is GOOD, wings that are cooked, and salads that look fresh, please do yourself the favor of going to New York New York in Ybor (they deliver to Seminole Heights) and spare yourself the potential hospital visit. Heights Pizza gives you all the convenience of delivery with the taste of a custom made, stone cooked, pie.  We found this restaurant while having a drink at Red Star Rock Bar (different review) and the delivery driver dropped off a couple pizzas and sandwiches for the bar staff.   It looked and smelled wonderful.  So we decided to give them a try a few nights later.   At the time they were struggling to keep up with their new-found fame and the delivery took about an hour and a half.  But the pizza was spectacular.  So we gave them a month to staff up.  Then we ordered again.  This time, the delivery took about an hour, and again the pizza was amazing.   Last night, we placed an order online,  and the pizza arrived in about 40 minutes.  Hot, fresh ingredients,  not over sauced, just another wonderful pizza.    Looks like they have fixed their delivery times. So, if you live in the Seminole Heights area, I would highly recommend you try Heights Pizza.  And if you don't live in the delivery area,  swing by one of the local Seminole Heights night spots and have the pizza delivered there....

My family and I were excited to try Heights Pizza based on reading the reviews on multiple sites and seeing their funny marketing ads on Twitter. When my son and I arrived it smelled like heaven. The employees were very nice. We left excited to eat a cheese, meat lovers and BBQ chicken pizza with their homemade sauce based on how amazing it smelled.However our excitement dimished as soon as we took a bite of the pizza. There was no sauce on any of the  pizzas. The crust on all three pizzas was very dense, stale, rock hard and had no taste. Low quality cheese, peperoni, ham and sausage. However the chicken and sausage on the BBQ Pizza that had no sauce was good but that was it. I have never been so disappointed in a meal before as I was tonight. If you like sauce and crust that has a rise, soft and is chewy then this is so not the place to go. If you like good quality toppings and cheese on your pizzas this is so not your place. Sigh such high hopes for this pizza place but not anymore.
